article.headline: East Tennessee State 73, North Carolina-Asheville 65
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. (AP) -- Courtney Pigram scored 17 points and East Tennessee State led all the way in beating N.C.-Asheville 73-65 Tuesday night. ETSU (7-5) led 29-7 with 9:50 left in the first half and was ahead by as much as 26, or 48-22, at the 18:06 mark. The Bulldogs (4-7) made the last 10 points to cut the final margin to 9. Andrew Reed added 15 points for East Tennessee, playing its first game in 10 days. Teammate Brad Nuckles scored 12 and Eryk Thomas had 11 and a team-high seven rebounds. Bryant Smithson led N.C.-Asheville with 14 points and Vincent James scored 11. East Tennessee shot 45.3 percent from the floor to 38.1 percent for the Bulldogs. The Bucs totaled a season-high 17 steals and forced 25 turnovers.
